\par }\pard\plain \s15\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\b\f1 How to uninstall a program?
\par }{\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\f1 1. Locate the program you wish to uninstall in the list and select it.
\par 2. Click the }{\i\f1 Add/Remove}{\f1  item from the menu located to the left of the list (or double-click the program name in the list).
\par 3. A dialog box will be displayed prompting you to continue or cancel. Click the Uninstall button.
\par 4. Add/Remove Plus! will run the uninstall routine of the program.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s15\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\f1 If the uninstall routine does not remove the program from the Add/Remove Programs list Add/Remove Plus! will prompt you to remove it.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1 How to remove a program from the list?
\par }{\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\f1 1. Locate the program in the list and select it.
\par 2. Click the }{\i\f1 Delete Entry}{\f1  item from the menu located to the left of the list.
\par }\pard\plain \s15\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\f1 
\par }{\b\f1 How to modify a list entry?
\par }{\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\f1 1. Locate the program in the list and select it.
\par 2. Click the }{\i\f1 Modify Entry}{\f1  item from the menu located to the left of the list.
\par }\pard\plain \s15\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\f1 3. Edit the program name or the uninstall command and click OK to apply changes.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1 How to add a new program to the list?
\par }{\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\f1 1. Click the }{\i\f1 New Entry}{\f1  item from the menu located to the left of the list.
\par }\pard\plain \s15\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\f1 3. Enter the program name and the uninstall command and click OK to add the new entry to the list.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1 The Setup program created a shortcut for the uninstall program, but did not create an entry in the Add/Remove Programs list. Can Add/Remove Plus! help me?}{\f1 
\par 
\par Sure. Just drag the Uninstall program shortcut from Explorer and drop it over the Add/Remove Plus! window. Add/Remove Plus! will add it to the list of programs that can be uninstalled from your computer.
